result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Jayson R HANSEN was found guilty of OWI (7th, 8th or 9th), a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
WAIVER OF PRELIMINARY HEARING -
Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 1 for further proceedings.   
ARRAIGNMENT
Information filed.

Count 1, OWI 7th offense - Guilty plea.  Convicted.  
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, P.A.C.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.
The defendant is found eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) pay $800.00 fine plus costs, total of $2,071.00.  $2,000.00 cash bail to be applied;
2) maintain absolute sobriety;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) submit a DNA sample;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court imposes a thirty-six (36) month license revocation and ignition interlock for period of revocation.
Minutes.
